@node "Présentation" "Overview"

 @{b}@{u}Overview@{ub}@{uu}

 BSound is a player for IFF-8SVX file sound (not compressed).


 @{i}@{u}It have many features:@{ui}@{uu}

 - OS 2.04 and more.

 - Play sound direct to disk (size of sample is unlimited).

 - Normal window or @{"BGUI" link "bgui.library" 0} window.

 - On Workbench, use the @{"ScreenNotify.library" link "ScreenNotify.library" 0} if present.

 - Use the iffparse.library for scanning file.

 - Arexx port for change Volume (Left, Right or Both), Filter... on the fly!

 - Small size !

 - Localised.

 - ToolTypes (WB), ReadArgs (CLI).

 - Restore filter after closing audio (another bug on system :'-( ).
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"

 @{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

 Just copy the BSound executable where you want. And check if you  are  the
 @{"bgui.library" link "bgui.library" 0}.
@endnode

@node "Paramčtres" "Parameters"

 @{b}@{u}Parameters@{ub}@{uu}

 The parameters of BSound can be modified with the tooltypes of its icon or
 in the icon of the sound.

 @{b}@{u}ToolType                               CLI                        @{ub}@{uu}


 @{fg shine}READALL=YES|NO                         READALL@{fg text}

    Load the entire sample in memory.


 @{fg shine}SPEAKER=LEFT|RIGHT|BOTH|DONTCARE       LEFT or RIGHT or BOTH@{fg text}

    Whick speaker we will use ??
    BOTH is great for play mono-sample on the 2 speaker.


 @{fg shine}FILTER=YES|NO                          FILTER=YES|NO@{fg text}

    Set the filter, or no.


 @{fg shine}LOOP=YES|NO                            LOOP@{fg text}

    Enable playing sample in loop mode.


 @{fg shine}SPEED=<NUMBER>                         SPEED=<NUMBER>@{fg text}

    Force a speed for the sample.


 @{fg shine}VOLUME=<NUMBER>                        VOLUME=<NUMBER>@{fg text}

    Set a volume. (0 to 64).


 @{fg shine}BUFSIZE=<NUMBER>                       BUFSIZE=<NUMBER>@{fg text}

    Set the size of the buffer.


 @{fg shine}SMALLWINDOW=YES|NO                     SMALLWINDOW@{fg text}

    Window will be a small window.


 @{fg shine}QUIET=YES|NO                           QUIET@{fg text}

    No GUI. :'-(.


 @{fg shine}PUBSCREEN=<NAME>                       PUBSCREEN=<NAME>@{fg text}

    Open BSound window on which public screen ?
@endnode

@node "Interface" "GUI"

 @{b}@{u}GUI@{ub}@{uu}

 @{u}o BGUI Window@{uu}

    A nice window, with the name of file and the level.
    A STOP button for quit.


 @{u}o Small window@{uu}

    A very small window, close it for quit.
@endnode

